pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.3.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Release 0.3.0 — proper multi-copy with leader-once-and-cut-between.
    - Print path migrated from ptouch-print (CLI) to nbuchwitz/ptouch
      via a downstream fork that adds PT-P710BT support. The new path
      submits one print job with N raster pages, a single leading edge,
      and a full cut between each copy — what ptouch-print physically
      cannot do (it re-finalises per copy, replicating the 24 mm leader).
    - Side margins (left/right) controllable in mm.
    - Horizontal preview with dimension arrows showing tape height
      (12 mm physical, with printable area inset) and label length.
    - "Fill tape height" toggle; conservative auto-size by default.
    - Modal font picker with live samples per font, Hebrew samples for
      Hebrew faces, filter box.
    - Preview vertical centering uses tight ink bounds so digits / caps
      no longer drift toward the bottom of the printable area.

 -- Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.co.il>  Tue, 19 May 2026 00:16:24 +0300

pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.2.0-9) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Remove CUPS backend (the page-size handling kept fighting us).
  * Switch the print path to nbuchwitz/ptouch via the patched fork that
    adds PT-P710BT support. `print_multi` sends one job with N pages
    and a single leader, full-cut between each label — what ptouch-print
    physically can't do.
  * Interpreter discovery: env override $PT_P710BT_LABEL_GUI_NB_PYTHON,
    then the known venv at ~/repos/github/nbuchwitz-ptouch/.venv, then
    system python3.

 -- Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.co.il>  Tue, 19 May 2026 00:12:03 +0300

pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.2.0-8) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Drop the backend selector — CUPS is now the only print path. The
    GUI requires the philpem printer-driver-ptouch with a configured
    PT-P710BT CUPS queue.
  * Fix CUPS scaling: render the print PNG ourselves in portrait
    orientation (W = tape width, H = label length) at the printer's
    native 180 DPI, then pass a Custom CUPS PageSize matching the
    PNG exactly so the driver doesn't scale to the PPD's fixed
    100 mm page length.

 -- Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.co.il>  Tue, 19 May 2026 00:01:45 +0300

pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.2.0-7) unstable; urgency=medium

