pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.2.0-5) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Revert v0.2.0-4's chain+precut handling — that produced one glued strip
    (precut once, then all copies back-to-back with no cut between),
    appearing as a single label.
  * Multi-copy with auto-cut now runs N separate ptouch-print invocations
    again (clean cut per copy; the ~24 mm leading bleed per copy is
    physical and unavoidable).
  * Updated Copies tooltip: with auto-cut OFF (chain mode) all copies print
    as one continuous strip with no wasted tape — user cuts manually.

