pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.2.0-4) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Multi-copy print now uses chain + precut + --copies=N in a single
    ptouch-print invocation, so the printer's ~24 mm leading-edge bleed
    happens once for the whole batch instead of being replicated per copy.
    Cuts still fire between labels. No final cut — pull/manual-cut the
    last label off.
  * Tooltip on the Copies field explains the chain-mode behaviour.

 -- Daniel Rosehill <daniel@danielrosehill.co.il>  Mon, 18 May 2026 23:23:38 +0300

pt-p710bt-label-gui (0.2.0-3) unstable; urgency=medium

  * Fix soft preview vertical centering: text was drifting toward the bottom
    of the printable area for digit-only / all-caps labels because Qt
    centred on font ascent/descent (which reserves descender space) rather
    than on visible ink. Now centred on tightBoundingRect.
  * Slightly more conservative default auto-size (0.55 of tape height,
    was 0.60) for a bit more visual margin.

